A police officer died after he chocked on a piece of meat in Tetu, Nyeri county. Constable Samson Nyakundi, 50, who was stationed at Ithekahuno police patrol base, bought meat at 2pm on Wednesday and went home to celebrate the festivities. But while eating it he got choked and colleagues rushed him to Nyeri
Referral Hospital, where he died while undergoing treatment. The body was transferred to Mathari Mission Hospital mortuary. Area police boss Job Lesikinwa said the officer collapsed while eating lunch. Nyakundi has served in Tetu for many years.      